Both fawns had been fed on with body cavities opened and consumed but substantial portion of meat on legs remaining. Both consistent with cluster date. However, the drag trail consisted of many tufts of coarse, crinkly hair that appeared to be from an adult ungulate. I was able to follow the trail in a looping fashion for ~100m before I ran out of hair. The hair appeared to end at the cached fawn. There was also the skeleton of an old kill that was at least a few months old (Completely picked over, no fresh meat remaining, bone marrow was dry and withered).
